flowRoot.flowPara: The International Day against Nuclear Tests, observed on August 29, commemmorates the closure of the Semipalatinsk Nuclear Test site in Kazahkstan on 29 August 1991. The resolution, passed in December 2, 2009 at the 64th session of the United Nations General Assembly, calls for increasing awareness about the impact of nuclear weapon test explosions or any other nuclear explosions and the need for their cessation as the means to achieving the goal of a nuclear-weapon-free world.
